Programming Languages:

Python: Primary language for machine learning (ML) and AI development.
Bash: For scripting and automation.
SQL: For managing and querying databases.
Frameworks and Libraries:

TensorFlow/PyTorch: For building neural networks and deep learning models.
Scikit-learn: For traditional ML algorithms like Random Forests, SVM, etc.
Hugging Face Transformers: For attention mechanisms and NLP tasks.
Django/Flask: For creating APIs to interact with the models.
Celery: For task scheduling and distributed processing.
Data Handling and Processing:

Pandas and NumPy: For data manipulation and numerical operations.
BeautifulSoup/Scrapy: For web scraping.
Airflow: For orchestrating data pipelines.
Infrastructure and Deployment:

Docker: For containerizing applications.
Kubernetes: For managing containerized applications.
AWS/GCP/Azure: Cloud platforms for scalable deployment.
Terraform: For infrastructure as code.
Version Control and CI/CD:

Git/GitHub/GitLab: For version control.
Jenkins/GitLab CI: For continuous integration and deployment.

Resource Management:
Prometheus/Grafana: For monitoring and resource management.
Ray/Dask: For parallel and distributed computing.
